The girl fetched a long, silent breath.
They were inside the reef, in comparatively smooth water, and to her ignorance they were safe.
But the rain would be coming in another moment, and Mrs. Maynard would be drenched; and Grace would be to blame for her death.
She ran to the closet, and pulled down her mother's India-rubber cloak and her own, and fled out-of-doors, to be ready on the beach with the wrap, against their landing.
