She was not in need of restoration.
She was perfectly alive, and apparently stimulated by her escape from deadly peril to a vivid conception of the wrong that had been done her.
If the adventure had passed off prosperously, she was the sort of woman to have owned to her friend that she ought not to have thought of going.
