She rather flaunted the happiness of her reunion in the face of the public, and she vouchsafed an explanation to no one.
There had never been anything definite in her charges against him, even to Grace, and her tacit withdrawal of them succeeded perfectly well.
The ladies, after some cynical tittering, forgot them, and rejoiced in the spectacle of conjugal harmony afforded them: women are generous creatures, and there is hardly any offence which they are not willing another woman should forgive her husband, when once they have said that they do not see how she could ever forgive him.
